          "scid": "thig2.6:1.0.3",
          "en": "6. Mettikā"
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig2.6:1.0.4",
          "en": "“Though I be suffering and weak, and all My youthful spring be gone, yet have I come, Leaning upon my staff, and clomb aloft The mountain peak."
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig2.6:1.0.5",
          "en": "My cloak thrown off, My little bowl o’erturned: so sit I here Upon the rock. And o’er my spirit sweeps The breath of Liberty! I win, I win The Triple Lore! The Buddha’s will is done!”"
        }
      ],
